title: For Sale:  Magpul UBR Stock, Magpul MIAD Pistol Grip and sling for your AR
postcontent:
This ad is for one stock and one grip in either black or FDE. Buy this set and I will toss in a Black Rain Ordnance Single point sling(real nice). I have a couple of these sets left over so they are available. Total value is well over $320.00. Please include your phone number if you would like a response, to many scammers. I check my email twice a day, morning and evening. Can do shipping in a medium flat rate box for around $14.00, I believe. I will check on other shipping options. Price for the stock, grip and sling is $240.00 not including shipping if desired. 

From Magpul: The Magpul UBR (Utility / Battle Rifle), U.S. Patent 6651371, is a fully-featured, adjustable buttstock for the AR15/M16. Unlike typical collapsing stocks, this modular design offers the stability of a fixed stock with consistent cheek weld in any position. Seven-position length-of-pull (LOP) adjustment is quickly executed with gross motor movement while the integral preset system allows direct access to a preferred position. A robust lock mechanism and multi-shell construction increase durability under severe impact conditions experienced during malfunction clearing and accommodates large-bore AR calibers with ease. The UBR also provides extra counterbalance weight to improve handling on full-length rifles and weapons with muzzle-heavy accessories or bull-barrels. Optional components such as dual-side sling mounts and metal strike plate allow the UBR to adapt to the mission at hand. https://www.magpul.com/products/ubr-collapsible-stock

The MIAD (MIssion ADaptable) Grip is a drop-in replacement for the standard AR15 grip. It is designed to improve ergonomics with interchangeable front and rear straps for personalized hand fit, an aggressive texture for positive weapon control, and is compatible with all Magpul grip cores to adapt to various storage needs. Made in U.S.A.


From me: You either need a stock to be solid and dependable, or you want a little more; there is very little in between, because the people that need a stock to stand up to breaching, shouldn't be buying a budget stock. This stock is one of Magpul's finest offerings and its retail price reflects that, but you get a dependable, tough, butt stock that can get you out of a pinch and you're not going to have to worry if it will or won't perform. Fit and finish are typical high quality Magpul and the UBR is solid as a rock. If you're looking for more than a shoulder prop, this is the stock you should buy.

I do not have the factory box for the stocks, as I had a number of these shipped to me in one box to save on shipping. These are the real deal, not knock off or reproductions. You have my guarantee. Let me know if you have any questions, I can send additional photo's as well.

title: For Sale/Trade:  16x7 heavy duty tandem axle trailer
postcontent:
I have a trailer that I have been building for quite some time and have decided to part ways. The main frame was salvaged from a old mobile home and then braced with 6 very heavy walled square crossbeams. The deck is made of true 2" thick rough sawed pine and treated with many coats of Thompsons to ward off rot. Overall deck length is 16 foot, with 12 foot being full width, and the overall width is 7 foot, with 6 1/2 foot between the inside rail lips. This trailer has dual 6600 lb axles, front axle has 12" electric brakes, all new brake parts, new 2800 lb rated 6 lug hubs and brake drums (cost me over $400 from Northern Tool), good 2800 lb rated 225/75-15 trailer tires (not car tires) and each of the 4 springs are rated at 3000 pounds. Also included is one pair of heavy duty homemade ramps that hook to the rear lip on the deck, ramps are made from the same mobile home steel with deck boards carriage bolted to them. The trailer comes with a 2 5/16" coupler and a pair of magnet towing lights that require a 4 wire flat plug. The hitch height sits at 22" for a level deck when unloaded, so your tow ball should be around that same height.

This trailer is not just some slap together hack job. I actually took the time to make sure the frame was completely square, the center point of the axles is exactly where it should be and perfectly matched from side to side. The hitch is perfectly centered and level with the frame. When on level ground the trailer will sit level without the jack, that way when properly loaded your tongue weight is acceptable and your vehicle just has to pull the trailer and leave all the hauling to the trailer's suspension.

What the trailer needs:
Permanent lighting
Lights and brakes wired
Fenders if you desire them (standard 66" long tandem fenders will do it)
Titled (I have always used it with a "FARM USE" tag)

I will take $750 cash or trade
